The paper deals with the analysis of document collections and the inference of themes/topics. This falls under the broad category of natural language processing (NLP), which is covered by cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of a hierarchical model to analyze annotated documents, which is a common technique in machine learning and statistics, covered by cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the use of a Poisson model, which is a common technique in probabilistic modeling, covered by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
